'''TIme-dependent neutronics and temperatures''' ('''TINTE''') is a two-group diffusion code for the study of nuclear and thermal behavior of high temperature reactors.  It was developed by [[Forschungszentrum Jülich]] in Germany, formally known as KFA ({{Lang-de|Kernforschungsanlage}}), to investigate [[Very high temperature reactor|HTGRs]] in 2D (r-Z) geometry.

